name: Squat Hold
startingPosition: Standing with feet slightly wider than hip distance
description:
1. Bend knees while keeping in line with feet, keep abs engaged 
2. Hold

name: Squat Pulse
startingPosition: Standing with feet slightly wider than hip distance
description:
1. Bend knees while keeping in line with feet, keep abs engaged 
2. Straighten knees slightly from starting squat position 
3. Bend knees slightly deeper than starting squat position 
4. Repeat as pulses

name: One Leg Step-ups
description:
1. Move one leg onto raised surface 
2. Transfer weight into raised surface leg 
3. Lift floor leg off floor, fully stand on raised surface leg 
4. Return floor leg to floor

name: One Leg Backwards Lunges
description:
1. Transfer weight into one leg (Standing Leg) 
2. Step non-Standing Foot backwards so that Standing Leg knee is bent at a 90 degree angle with knee over ankle 
3. Return to starting position

name: Air Squats
description:
1. Bend elbows to 90 degrees while maintaining a straight line from head to feet 
 2. Push back up to starting position

name: Squat Jumps
startingPosition: Standing with feet slightly wider than hip distance
description:
1. Squat down 
2. Jump upwards 
3. Land in squat position

name: Pistol Squats
description:
1. Transfer weight into one leg (Standing Leg) 
2. With all weight on Standing Leg sit down onto raised surface while lifting non-Standing Leg 
3. Return to standing position

name: One Leg Forward Lunges
description:
1. Transfer weight into one leg (Standing Leg) 
2. Step non-Standing Leg forward so that knee is at a 90 degree angle 
3. Push back to starting position

name: One Leg Side Lunges
description:
1. Transfer weight into one leg (Standing Leg) 
2. Step non-Standing Leg sideways so that knee is at a 90 degree angle 
3. Push back to starting position

name: Burpees
description:
1. Jump up 
2. Put hands on floor and jump feet backwards to plank 
3. Jump feet forwards to hands and stand up 
4. Repeat

name: Calf Lifts
startingPosition: Standing with feet shoulder width apart
description:
1. Transfer weight into toes 
2. Push up onto tippy toes 
3. Return to flat feet

name: Toe Taps
description:
1. Rest toes of one foot on raised surface 
2. Switch to other toes on raised surface 
3. Repeat quickly
